---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Dissertation — Spatial Prioritisation for Red Squirrel Conservation"
  description="Spatial prioritisation framework for red squirrel conservation under pine marten recolonisation in Cumbria."
>
  <Navbar slot="nav" />

  <article>
    <!-- Project banner -->
    <header class="project-banner">
      <div class="banner-bg" style={`background-image: url('${base}images/dissertation/algorithm_strongholds.png')`}></div>
      <div class="banner-overlay"></div>
      <div class="container banner-content">
        <a href={`${base}projects`} class="back-link">← All Projects</a>
        <div class="banner-meta">
          <span class="grade-badge">78 / 100</span>
          <span class="tag">Dissertation</span>
          <span class="tag">2025</span>
        </div>
        <h1>Please Marten the Gap</h1>
        <p class="banner-sub">Spatial Prioritisation for Red Squirrel Conservation</p>
        <div class="banner-tags">
          {["Python", "GeoPandas", "ArcGIS Pro", "MCDA", "Landscape Ecology"].map(t => (
            <span class="tag">{t}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container project-body">
      <div class="project-layout">
        <!-- Main content -->
        <div class="prose">

          <h2>Project Overview</h2>
          <p>
            Invasive grey squirrels have displaced native red squirrels from much of the United Kingdom,
            and culling programmes are increasingly controversial and underfunded. This dissertation develops
            a <strong>spatial prioritisation framework</strong> to guide red squirrel conservation as the
            <strong>native pine marten</strong> — a predator that selectively suppresses the invasive grey
            squirrel — recolonises Cumbria after being nearly functionally extinct since the 1700s.
          </p>
          <p>
            Working with open-source data and libraries, I built a Python-based algorithm that models how
            pine martens reduce grey squirrel densities and then ranks candidate strongholds using a
            <strong>multi-criteria decision analysis (MCDA)</strong>. Criteria include residual grey squirrel
            density, core habitat area, and management feasibility derived from landowner willingness proxies.
            By exploring trade-offs across three suppression scenarios (low, moderate, high), the study
            provides an evidence-based roadmap for NGOs allocating limited resources.
          </p>

          <h2>Motivation</h2>
          <p>
            This project was motivated by four core questions:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>How will grey squirrel distribution respond to pine marten recovery under different predation efficiencies?</li>
            <li>Where should conservation NGOs prioritise strongholds when balancing grey cost, core habitat area, and management feasibility?</li>
            <li>How robust are existing policies such as the Lake District Stronghold Complex when predator dynamics change?</li>
            <li>How can a transparent modelling framework build trust with stakeholders and adapt to new ecological data?</li>
          </ol>

          <h2>Methodology</h2>
          <p>
            The analysis integrates landscape ecology, geospatial programming, and computational decision-making:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Suppression modelling:</strong> Baseline grey squirrel densities were reduced using three pine marten suppression coefficients derived from field studies. The residual density surface becomes the grey cost criterion in the MCDA.</li>
            <li><strong>Habitat and feasibility mapping:</strong> High-resolution land cover and woodland data were reclassified to identify suitable habitat patches. Each 100 m grid cell receives a feasibility score from 1 (Low) to 4 (High) based on grant uptake, Countryside Stewardship schemes, and Forestry England ownership.</li>
            <li><strong>Cluster-based MCDA:</strong> A custom greedy algorithm grows clusters of habitat patches from seed sites, scoring each cluster across grey cost, core area, and feasibility. Thousands of candidate strongholds are evaluated per suppression scenario.</li>
            <li><strong>Correlation analysis:</strong> Examined how the influence of each criterion shifts with suppression level — revealing adaptive management insights.</li>
          </ul>

          <figure>
            <img src={`${base}images/dissertation/code.png`} alt="Workflow diagram — suppression modelling, clustering, and MCDA scoring" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Figure 1: Workflow diagram showing suppression modelling, clustering, and MCDA scoring.</figcaption>
          </figure>

          <h2>Results</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Whinlatter Forest</strong> is consistently identified as the top stronghold across all scenarios.</li>
            <li>An expanded <strong>Greystoke</strong> site ranks second under low suppression; <strong>Elterwater</strong> emerges as robust across scenarios.</li>
            <li>Significant suppression shifts priority away from conifer plantations toward broadleaf and mixed woodlands, challenging current policy.</li>
            <li>Correlation analysis shows grey cost drives scores when grey squirrels are abundant; core habitat area rises in importance as suppression increases.</li>
          </ul>

          <figure>
            <img src={`${base}images/dissertation/algorithm_strongholds.png`} alt="Algorithmically selected strongholds map" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Figure 2: Algorithmically selected strongholds across suppression scenarios.</figcaption>
          </figure>

          <figure>
            <img src={`${base}images/dissertation/Xray.png`} alt="Grey squirrel density comparison under suppression scenarios" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Figure 3: Grey squirrel density in existing strongholds under low, moderate, and high pine marten suppression.</figcaption>
          </figure>

          <figure>
            <img src={`${base}images/dissertation/graph.png`} alt="Stronghold analysis — habitat composition, core area, and grey squirrel density" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Figure 4: Stronghold analysis investigating how prioritised habitat composition, core area, and grey squirrel density change under suppression scenarios.</figcaption>
          </figure>

          <h2>Implications for NGOs</h2>
          <p>
            The framework provides ranked woodland complexes accounting for ecological impact and local feasibility,
            helping NGOs target limited resources effectively. All code is open-source and replicable, fostering
            collaboration and trust among stakeholders. The scenario outputs enable phased investment planning
            aligned with predator recovery timelines.
          </p>

          <h2>Final Reflection</h2>
          <p>
            The study demonstrates that embracing a returning predator can transform invasive species management.
            By linking pine marten recovery with a transparent prioritisation tool, it moves beyond theoretical
            discourse to provide actionable guidance for NGOs — revealing hidden trade-offs between ecology and
            feasibility, challenging assumptions about conifer-dominated reserves, and proposing adaptive pathways
            that align with human and ecological realities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <aside class="project-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Resources</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/projects/dissertation/FINAL_SUBMISSION.pdf" target="_blank" class="sidebar-link">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/>
                  <polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/>
                </svg>
                Full Dissertation (PDF)
              </a>
              <a href="https://github.com/MaxLarner/spatial_prioritisation" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="sidebar-link">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
                  <path d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.477 2 12c0 4.418 2.865 8.166 6.839 9.489.5.092.682-.217.682-.482 0-.237-.009-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.604-3.369-1.342-3.369-1.342-.454-1.154-1.11-1.462-1.11-1.462-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.03 1.531 1.03.892 1.529 2.341 1.087 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.11-4.555-4.943 0-1.091.39-1.984 1.029-2.683-.103-.253-.446-1.27.098-2.647 0 0 .84-.269 2.75 1.025A9.578 9.578 0 0 1 12 6.836a9.59 9.59 0 0 1 2.504.337c1.909-1.294 2.747-1.025 2.747-1.025.546 1.377.202 2.394.1 2.647.64.699 1.028 1.592 1.028 2.683 0 3.842-2.339 4.687-4.566 4.935.359.309.678.919.678 1.852 0 1.336-.012 2.415-.012 2.743 0 .267.18.578.688.48C19.138 20.163 22 16.418 22 12c0-5.523-4.477-10-10-10z"/>
                </svg>
                Source Code on GitHub
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Skills Demonstrated</h3>
            <ul class="sidebar-skills">
              <li>Geospatial programming (2,000+ line Python workflow)</li>
              <li>Landscape ecology metrics</li>
              <li>Multi-criteria decision analysis</li>
              <li>Feasibility assessment & stakeholder proxies</li>
              <li>Raster and vector processing</li>
              <li>Scientific communication</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Banner */
  .project-banner {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 420px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-end;
    padding-top: var(--nav-h);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .banner-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    filter: saturate(0.4) brightness(0.35);
  }

  .banner-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(8,13,24,1) 0%, rgba(8,13,24,0.5) 60%, rgba(8,13,24,0.2) 100%);
  }

  .banner-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-3);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    transition: color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .back-link:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .banner-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .banner-content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .banner-sub {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-2);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .banner-tags { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.4rem; }

  /* Layout */
  .project-body { padding-top: 3.5rem; padding-bottom: 2rem; }

  .project-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 300px;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* Sidebar */
  .project-sidebar { position: sticky; top: calc(var(--nav-h) + 2rem); }

  .sidebar-card {
    background: var(--bg-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .sidebar-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-3);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .sidebar-links { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }

  .sidebar-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-2);
    transition: color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .sidebar-link:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .sidebar-skills {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .sidebar-skills li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-2);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .sidebar-skills li::before {
    content: "→";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .project-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.5rem; }
    .project-sidebar { position: static; }
  }
</style>
